cyclone.name: HUMBERTO
cyclone.current_location: about 130 mi ESE of Great Abaco Island
cyclone.trajectory: Moving northwest and then north-northwest, expected to skirt the north-western Bahamas Saturday and track just offshore the Florida east coast this weekend before turning northward off the Southeast U.S. coast early next week
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: No U.S. landfall expected – closest approach offshore of the east-central to northeast Florida coastline

weather_observation.impacted_coast: Atlantic coast from central Florida northward through South Carolina
weather_observation.wind: Brief periods of tropical-storm-force gusts (primarily in squalls) possible Sunday into early Monday; sustained winds mostly below gale force.
weather_observation.storm_surge: Minor surge possible (<2 ft) around times of high tide.
weather_observation.rainfall: 2–4 inches of rain Sunday–Monday could cause localized ponding and minor drainage issues.
weather_observation.other_hazards: High surf and dangerous rip currents along area beaches impacting pilot operations and small-craft movements.
